TrueLook mediates between Internet users and visual resources on the network, including live cameras, video / photo databases, and tools for using and sharing pictures and video. Through PRI's TrueLook software solutions, users interact with telerobotic web cameras to view whatever they'd like, just as if they were actually present in that place. And, TrueLook software allows multiple users to experience a single location at once, up to the limits of the network bandwidth. Users receive high-end, still JPEG, photographic-quality images within seconds of whatever they choose to see, even over lower-bandwidth modems. Description: Modus 3D, a revenue generating company, produces highly accurate 3D data above and below ground complemented.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Denver Area, Western US
Full Description: Modus 3D, a revenue generating company, produces highly accurate 3D data above and below ground complemented with a cloud-based geospatial 3D visualization software for asset management. The world is experiencing a 3D phenomenon. Modus 3D is on the cutting edge of this revolution, with their powerful geospatial tool that has unmatched capabilities and has been proclaimed to be the first to market. The Modus 3D business model is predicated on enhancing the 3D visualization platform for three primary national and international markets: Oil and Gas, A/E/C, (Architecture, Engineering, Construction) and Critical Infrastructure. For the past years, the company specialized in geospatial 3D field data collection of capital assets using 3D data collection in laser and radar technology. Modus recently obtained the Intellectual Property rights to a one-of-a-kind 3D visualization cloud-based mobile application. Modus is revolutionizing asset rich industries with the most unique cloud-based 3D visualization tool.  Software Product: 3D Geospatial Visualization Tool: Their technology is the first to integrate CAD and GIS data into a single pane for analysis and annotation of assets. With many unique features, you can bring in live camera feeds and real time sensor information.  Supporting Services: LiDAR (Light Detection And Ranging) laser scanners are capable of capturing building interiors and exteriors, roads and bridges, refineries and airports with an accuracy if 1/8 inch. GPR (Ground Penetrating Radar) scanner will capture data below ground to 100 feet and typically scanning to 15 feet with 2 inch accuracy. UAV Aerial Photogrammetry; The quick and nimble UAV's are the wave of the future in capturing the most up ground imagery with less cost and fast delivery. 3D Modeling: Most importantly, after field data collection from Laser, Radar and UAV's is completed, they process the data and create high definition, highly accurate geospatially correct, solid 3D models.

Description: BeeJooS serves as an online destination where fashion meets travel.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: The idea of BeeJooS (Aborigine for jewelry) was conceptualized by our Mauritian-born, London-bred, New York-residing founder. On a voyage of discovery back from Vietnam, it dawned upon her that as the world gets flatter, the "global citizen" (the fastest growing population in the world) increasingly craves a global lifestyle experience platform. Combining her passion for continent-hopping (over 40 countries and counting!!!) and keen eye for curating exotic accessories, our founder aimed to fulfill this need….And BeejooS was born!!!   BeeJooS serves as an online destination where fashion meets travel, providing shoppers access to lifestyle accessories from eclectic bazaars and emerging designers from across the world. BeeJooS is uniquely positioned to provide you with timeless and decadent accessories at affordable prices right at your doorstep. We travel around the globe in search of one-of-a-kind statement pieces and handpick our products based on how best they reflect local customs and specific cultural nuances of the country of origin. In short, we seek to be a provider of global fashion locally and bring out the global citizen in you.   Keeping in mind our goal to be the best online portal for providing "fashion meets travel" lifestyle experience, we also feature a travel blog that provides content and insight into whats new and whats hot in terms of alternative travel experience and local travel secrets. We seek to constantly educate our shoppers on hidden itineraries in featured destinations, including go-to sauce spots, off-beat local dining, secret martini dens and unique lodging venues. Our theme of "Shop, Support and Savor The Globe" is based on our belief that one’s passion for global fashion and travel need not be mutually exclusive. BeeJooS’s mission is to provide our "global citizen" shoppers with a single-door access to affordable and alternative fashion and travel experience.   BeeJooS is structured as a social enterprise and seeks to support its designer and artisan community globally. In addition to providing its designers and artisans with an online marketplace, BeeJooS also pledges to donate a portion of the proceeds to charities that address the most pertinent, ground-level social and economic issues of their local communities.

Description: Spray Nine is a cleaning solution brand for household and professional use.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: In 1956, the Spray Nine Corporation became the first company to package a cleaning solution in a spray bottle. This made cleaning faster and much easier by eliminating the need to mix chemicals with water. Due to Spray Nine, an entirely new product category was created – the ready-to-use, spray-on/wipe-off cleaner. Spray Nine® was first used on automobiles to clean tires, whitewalls and upholstery with less effort. It was so good for cleaning cars that people soon began using it around the house. Due to Spray Nine’s popularity as a household cleaner, a disinfectant was added in 1968 to kill germs and viruses. Industrial and institutional markets quickly realized Spray Nine® was also ideal for professional use. Over the next three decades, Spray Nine® expanded to a full line of specialty cleaners for industrial, institutional, retail, automotive, marine and military/government applications. The company’s growth across diverse markets was fueled by a series of top rated products and industry firsts. Today, Spray Nine® leverages over 50 years of experience and service to provide specialty cleaners with unmatched performance, speed and economy. Spray Nine’s traditional cleaning products and green cleaning products are used throughout Canada, United States and Europe. Strong brand loyalty ensures that Spray Nine® products will remain a permanent force in the cleaning industry.
